<h1>Problem 1977 - 2023 IMOSL, G3, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(ABCD\) be a cyclic quadrilateral with \(\angle BAD < \angle ADC\). Let \(M\) be the midpoint of the arc \(CD\) not containing \(A\). Suppose there is a point \(P\) inside \(ABCD\) such that \(\angle ADB =\angle CPD\) and \(\angle ADP =\angle PCB\). Prove that lines \(AD\), \(PM\), \(BC\) are concurrent.</p>
